  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Adolescent support center</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project will provide a safe environment for adolescent girls (13-18) in the Al-Shama camps and Dream city complex , through the opening of the center (the support and development of adolescent) in both camps, that provides psychological support to the 1000 girls within six months, through implementation of entertainment and education activities and learn life skills and crafts such as sewing, knitting, painting, acting,referal in addition to the awareness program for the families in the camps, which focuses on the importance of providing protection for young girls during the period of emergency and how to deal with them and against early marriage, who works on the violation of their rights.
Center (Support and development of adolescent), it would be safe haven for them to express themselves, talk about their problems and the development of life skills and rehabilitation for their entry in life more confidence, the activities will help it provided to overcome the trauma they have suffered during displacement, and overcome the hard life in the camps,
the center also will support young girls subjected to harassment and sexual assault, or wrongful sexual practices by the girls with the boys of the same ages in the camp and practiced as a result of the vacuum, choking also the wrong understanding of the relationship and sexual and lack of interest in parents, the center will provide adequate support to these girls, in addition to the awareness of the dangers practices either on their bodies or their own lives in the future . as well as rehabilitation to protect themselves from these risks and restore their self-esteem through activities and events carried out by specialized staff in this field.</narrative>
  </description>
